@flexiarg coordination/pattern-search-protocol
@title Pattern Search Protocol (G3)
@keywords search, candidates, retrieval, compass, notions
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/minimum-viable-events futon-theory/proof-path]

! conclusion:
  If you want pattern selection to be reviewable and improvable, log the candidate search process (query, candidates, scores) as part of PSR evidence.

  + context: A PSR should explain not just the winner but the considered alternatives.
  + IF:
    you want pattern retrieval quality to improve over time

  + HOWEVER:
    without candidate logs, retrieval is a black box and failures cannot be debugged

  + THEN:
    record `:psr/candidates` and a short rationale in the PSR output of G3

  + BECAUSE:
    the search protocol is part of the evidence, and it feeds the glacial library evolution loop later

